Note:
CSS to HIR Translation Test Suite

Total Tests: 10
:End Note

Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/frontends/css/css_to_hir.runa" as Translator
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa" as StringCore

@Reasoning:
Counter triple shared across the CSS-to-HIR driver. Same layout as the
other CSS suites (parser, round-trip) so a unified runner can swap test
binaries with no struct conversion.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
total at offset 0, passed at 8, failed at 16; mutated via raw
Layout.memory_set_int64 because results is shared by handle.
@End Implementation

Type called "TestResults":
    total as Integer
    passed as Integer
    failed as Integer
End Type

@Reasoning:
Top-level driver for CSS-to-HIR translation. Calls 10 named test
processes, each covering a distinct CSS construct (rule, selectors,
at-rules, media query, comment, pseudo-class, attribute selector).
Distinct named test procs (rather than parameterized calls) make a
failure log immediately identify which CSS feature regressed.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Allocate TestResults, print banner, run all 10 test_* procs against
the shared results buffer, print summary, return 1 on any failure
else 0.
@End Implementation

@TestCases:
- All 10 named CSS forms translate to non-null HIR -> exit 0
- Any single test_* returns 0 -> results.failed >= 1 -> exit 1
@End TestCases

Process called "main" returns Integer:
    Let results be a value of type TestResults with total as 0, passed as 0, failed as 0

    proc print_header

    proc test_simple_rule from results
    proc test_class_selector from results
    proc test_id_selector from results
    proc test_multiple_selectors from results
    proc test_multiple_declarations from results
    proc test_at_rule from results
    proc test_media_query from results
    proc test_comment from results
    proc test_pseudo_class from results
    proc test_attribute_selector from results

    proc print_results from results

    If results.failed is greater than 0:
        Return 1
    End If

    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Baseline smoke test for the translator: a single type selector with one
declaration. If translate_css_to_hir cannot handle this canonical form,
nothing else will work, so this test is intentionally first.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Increment total. Build "div { color: red; }" via StringCore. Call
translate_css_to_hir(source, 0). Non-null result -> [PASS]+ passed
counter; null result -> [FAIL]+failed counter. Always frees source.
@End Implementation

@TestCases:
- Input "div { color: red; }" -> non-null HIR, results.passed += 1
- Translator returns 0 -> "Simple rule: failed", results.failed += 1
@End TestCases

Process called "test_simple_rule" takes results as Integer returns Integer:
    Let _rtot1 be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with results, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with results, 0, _rtot1 plus 1

    Let source be proc create_string from StringCore with "div { color: red; }"
    Let hir be proc translate_css_to_hir from Translator with source, 0

    If hir is not equal to 0:
        proc print_test_success with "Simple rule"
        proc deallocate from Layout with source
        Let _rpas1 be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with results, 8
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with results, 8, _rpas1 plus 1
        Return 1
    End If

    proc print_test_failure with "Simple rule: failed"
    proc deallocate from Layout with source
    Let _rfal1 be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with results, 16
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with results, 16, _rfal1 plus 1

    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Verifies the dot-prefix class selector path through the lexer and
translator. Class selectors are the most common CSS selector form,
so a regression here would block almost every real stylesheet.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Increment total. Build ".container { width: 100%; }". Call translator
with 0 arena. Branch on hir != 0; free source on both paths.
@End Implementation

@TestCases:
- Input ".container { width: 100%; }" -> non-null HIR, passed += 1
- Translator drops the "." prefix or fails -> failed += 1
@End TestCases

Process called "test_class_selector" takes results as Integer returns Integer:
