End Process

@Reasoning:
Verifies the hash-prefix ID selector path. Distinct from class
selectors in the lexer (# vs .) but identical in the parser, so this
test catches a token-class confusion regression that would let class
tests pass while ID selectors silently drop.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Increment total. Build "#main { padding: 20px; }". Call translator
with 0 arena. Branch on hir != 0; free source on both paths.
@End Implementation

@TestCases:
- Input "#main { padding: 20px; }" -> non-null HIR, passed += 1
- Lexer maps "#" to a non-ID token -> translator returns 0 -> failed += 1
@End TestCases

