@Reasoning:
Verifies that the declaration list inside one rule accepts three
property:value pairs separated by semicolons. Catches a parser
regression where the loop exits after the first declaration.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Increment total. Build "body { margin: 0; padding: 0; font-size: 16px; }".
Translator with 0 arena. Branch on hir != 0; free source on both paths.
@End Implementation

@TestCases:
- Input with three semicolon-separated declarations -> non-null HIR,
  passed += 1
- Parser drops the trailing two declarations -> translator may still
  succeed but failed += 1 if it returns 0
- Translator fails outright -> "Multiple declarations: failed", failed += 1
@End TestCases

