@Reasoning:
Verifies the single-colon pseudo-class form. The lexer must produce a
pseudo-class token when ":hover" follows an identifier without
whitespace; failure here means selector lexing is too aggressive at
splitting tokens.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Increment total. Build "a:hover { color: blue; }". Translator with
0 arena. Branch on hir != 0; free source on both paths.
@End Implementation

@TestCases:
- Input "a:hover { color: blue; }" -> non-null HIR with pseudo-class
  selector, passed += 1
- Lexer treats ":hover" as ":" then identifier -> translator may still
  succeed but selector semantics wrong; null HIR -> failed += 1
@End TestCases

