@Reasoning:
Verifies attribute selectors with [name="value"] syntax. Catches a
regression where the lexer treats "[" as an unrecognized token or the
parser fails to consume the matching "]", which would silently corrupt
the selector AST and cause downstream emitter problems.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Increment total. Build "input[type=\"text\"] { border: 1px solid #ccc; }".
Translator with 0 arena. Branch on hir != 0; free source on both paths.
@End Implementation

@TestCases:
- Input "input[type=\"text\"] { border: 1px solid #ccc; }" -> non-null
  HIR with attribute-selector node, passed += 1
- Lexer breaks on "[" or "=" inside selector -> translator returns 0
  -> failed += 1
@End TestCases

